    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-04-22T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-04-22T00:00:00-05:00" n="868"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d868">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.112 B61/51.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Consul</gloss> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Ciudad Juárez</hi> (<hi rend="italic">El Paso,
                                Tex.</hi>)</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-04-22">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 22, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Federal court of Mexico at Ciudad Juárez to-day released from custody
                    Lawrence Converse and Edward Blatt, arrested February 22 <pb facs="0694" n="612"
                        xml:id="pg_612"/> and charged with sedition and who claimed to have been
                    taken from American soil. The same court also released Richard Brown, the nurse
                    arrested February 26, also charged with sedition.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Thomas D. Edwards.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
